  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Al observar los histogramas de concentración total, se identifica un grupo pequeño de observaciones acumuladas cerca de cero. Estos valores se separan claramente del resto de la distribución, donde la mayoría de los registros presentan concentraciones totales bastante superiores.\n",
    "\n",
    "Por esta razón, se definió `ANOMALY_LIMIT = 5` como umbral para eliminar registros con concentraciones totales extremadamente bajas. El valor 5 permite capturar esos casos anómalos cercanos a cero sin afectar la parte principal de la distribución. Estos registros probablemente corresponden a errores de medición, fallos en el registro de datos o momentos donde el proceso no estaba operando normalmente.\n",
    "\n",
    "Eliminar estas observaciones es adecuado porque valores tan bajos de concentración total no son representativos del comportamiento normal del proceso de recuperación y podrían distorsionar el entrenamiento del modelo."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Construcción del modelo"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3.1. Funciones para calcular sMAPE y sMAPE final"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def smape(y_true, y_pred):\n",
    "    y_true = np.array(y_true)\n",
    "    y_pred = np.array(y_pred)\n",
    "    denominator = (np.abs(y_true) + np.abs(y_pred)) / 2\n",
    "    result = np.where(\n",
    "        denominator == 0,\n",
    "        0,\n",
    "        np.abs(y_true - y_pred) / denominator\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return np.mean(result) * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "def final_smape(y_true_rougher, pred_rougher, y_true_final, pred_final):\n",
    "    smape_rougher = smape(y_true_rougher, pred_rougher)\n",
    "    smape_final_stage = smape(y_true_final, pred_final)\n",
    "    return 0.25 * smape_rougher + 0.75 * smape_final_stage"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3.2. Preparación de variables para el modelo"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Features train: (13787, 52)\n",
      "Features test: (5153, 52)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "features_train = train_final[features_columns]\n",
    "target_train_rougher = train_final['rougher.output.recovery']\n",
    "target_train_final = train_final['final.output.recovery']\n",
    "\n",
    "features_test = test_final[features_columns]\n",
    "target_test_rougher = test_final['rougher.output.recovery']\n",
    "target_test_final = test_final['final.output.recovery']\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Features train:', features_train.shape)\n",
    "print('Features test:', features_test.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3.3. Validación cruzada"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "smape_scorer = make_scorer(\n",
    "    smape,\n",
    "    greater_is_better=False\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<div>\n",
       "<style scoped>\n",
       "    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n",
       "        vertical-align: middle;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    .dataframe tbody tr th {\n",
       "        vertical-align: top;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    .dataframe thead th {\n",
       "        text-align: right;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "</style>\n",
       "<table border=\"1\" class=\"dataframe\">\n",
       "  <thead>\n",
       "    <tr style=\"text-align: right;\">\n",
       "      <th></th>\n",
       "      <th>Modelo</th>\n",
       "      <th>sMAPE Rougher</th>\n",
       "      <th>sMAPE Final</th>\n",
       "      <th>sMAPE Total</th>\n",
       "    </tr>\n",
       "  </thead>\n",
       "  <tbody>\n",
       "    <tr>\n",
       "      <th>2</th>\n",
       "      <td>Random Forest</td>\n",
       "      <td>7.182076</td>\n",
       "      <td>9.801215</td>\n",
       "      <td>9.146430</td>\n",
       "    </tr>\n",
       "    <tr>\n",
       "      <th>0</th>\n",
       "      <td>Linear Regression</td>\n",
       "      <td>7.224944</td>\n",
       "      <td>10.961060</td>\n",
       "      <td>10.027031</td>\n",
       "    </tr>\n",
       "    <tr>\n",
       "      <th>1</th>\n",
       "      <td>Decision Tree</td>\n",
       "      <td>10.917514</td>\n",
       "      <td>15.940200</td>\n",
       "      <td>14.684529</td>\n",
       "    </tr>\n",
       "  </tbody>\n",
       "</table>\n",
       "</div>"
      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "              Modelo  sMAPE Rougher  sMAPE Final  sMAPE Total\n",
       "2      Random Forest       7.182076     9.801215     9.146430\n",
       "0  Linear Regression       7.224944    10.961060    10.027031\n",
       "1      Decision Tree      10.917514    15.940200    14.684529"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "models = {\n",
    "    'Linear Regression': LinearRegression(),\n",
    "    'Decision Tree': DecisionTreeRegressor(random_state=12345),\n",
    "    'Random Forest': RandomForestRegressor(random_state=12345)\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "results = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for name, model in models.items():\n",
    "\n",
    "    rougher_score = -cross_val_score(\n",
    "        model,\n",
    "        features_train,\n",
    "        target_train_rougher,\n",
    "        cv=5,\n",
    "        scoring=smape_scorer\n",
    "    ).mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "    final_score = -cross_val_score(\n",
    "        model,\n",
    "        features_train,\n",
    "        target_train_final,\n",
    "        cv=5,\n",
    "        scoring=smape_scorer\n",
    "    ).mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "    total_score = 0.25 * rougher_score + 0.75 * final_score\n",
    "\n",
    "    results.append([\n",
    "        name,\n",
    "        rougher_score,\n",
    "        final_score,\n",
    "        total_score\n",
    "    ])\n",
    "\n",
    "results = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    results,\n",
    "    columns=[\n",
    "        'Modelo',\n",
    "        'sMAPE Rougher',\n",
    "        'sMAPE Final',\n",
    "        'sMAPE Total'\n",
    "    ]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "results = results.sort_values('sMAPE Total')\n",
    "\n",
    "display(results)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "La función `make_scorer()` se utilizó para integrar la métrica sMAPE dentro de `cross_val_score()`. Como sMAPE no es una métrica incluida directamente en Scikit-Learn, fue necesario convertirla en una métrica compatible con el proceso de validación cruzada.\n",
    "\n",
    "Además, se configuró `greater_is_better=False` porque en este proyecto un menor valor de sMAPE representa un mejor desempeño del modelo. Por eso, al calcular los resultados se cambia el signo de los valores devueltos por `cross_val_score()`.\n",
    "\n",
    "La validación cruzada se realizó con cinco particiones (`cv=5`) para evaluar cada modelo de manera más estable. Luego se calculó el sMAPE total usando la ponderación definida en el proyecto: 25% para la etapa `rougher` y 75% para la etapa final."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3.4. Evaluación final en el conjunto de prueba"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "best_model_name = results.iloc[0]['Modelo']\n",
    "\n",
    "if best_model_name == 'Linear Regression':\n",
    "    best_model_rougher = LinearRegression()\n",
    "    best_model_final = LinearRegression()\n",
    "\n",
    "elif best_model_name == 'Decision Tree':\n",
    "    best_model_rougher = DecisionTreeRegressor(random_state=12345)\n",
    "    best_model_final = DecisionTreeRegressor(random_state=12345)\n",
    "\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    best_model_rougher = RandomForestRegressor(random_state=12345)\n",
    "    best_model_final = RandomForestRegressor(random_state=12345)\n",
    "\n",
    "best_model_rougher.fit(\n",
    "    features_train,\n",
    "    target_train_rougher\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "best_model_final.fit(\n",
    "    features_train,\n",
    "    target_train_final\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "pred_rougher = best_model_rougher.predict(features_test)\n",
